{
  "text": "ANNs are adaptive systems consisting of a number of simple processing elements (neurons), grouped into one or more layers, that are interconnected with adjustable parameters (synaptic weights). Modification of these adjustable parameters allows the ANN to learn an arbitrary vector mapping input space X to the output space y = f(X) [CITATION_1] .",
